== standard option state:
errtrace-on
functrace-on
braceexpand-on
hashall-on
keyword-on
== brace expansion follows its option:
<{a,b}>
<c>
<d>
== vi and emacs can both be off:
noninteractive-editing-off
vi-off
emacs-off
== command substitution isolates option state:
notify         	off
== runtime noexec stops later commands:
noexec-clean
nested-noexec-clean
noexec-loops-stop
== function option changes survive defining-mood state:
function-option-persisted
strict-markers-persisted
function-runtime-state-persisted
function-posix-persisted
function-posix-noop-stayed
substitution-revisions-isolated
== command strings publish c in dollar dash:
command-string
== interactive state is independent of hashall:
interactive
== command substitution isolates startup state:
startup-state-isolated
== command substitution preserves directory identity:
directory-identity-preserved
== command substitution restores a permission-revoked directory:
permission-directory-preserved
== command substitution enters from an execute-only directory:
execute-only-directory-preserved
== SHELLOPTS uses the shared option state:
braceexpand-listed
hashall-listed
shellopts-generated-order
== physical mode resolves a symlinked directory:
physical=yes
physical-cdpath=yes
physical-dotdot=yes
== cd uses native path syntax:
native-cdpath
native-dot-relative
native-absolute
